{"title_page": "Oceania Zonal Volleyball Association", "text_new": "{{Infobox organization\n| name                = Oceania Zonal Volleyball Association\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| map                 = Asian Volleyball Confederation Map.png\n| mcaption            = \n| abbreviation        = OZVA\n| motto               = \n| formation           = December 1993; {{Years or months ago|1993|12}}\n| type                = Sport organisation\n| headquarters        = \n| region_served       = [[Oceania]]\n| membership          = 20 member associations\n| language            = [[English language|English]] \n| leader_title        = President\n| leader_name         = {{flagdeco|COK}} Hugh Graham\n| parent_organization = [[Asian Volleyball Confederation|AVC]]\n| website             = [http://oceaniavolleyball.org/ OceaniaVolleyball.org]\n}}\n\nThe '''Oceania Zonal Volleyball Association (OZVA)''', is the [[sports governing body|governing body]] for the [[sport|sports]] of [[volleyball|indoor]], [[beach volleyball|beach]] and grass [[volleyball]] in [[Oceania]].\n\nIn the spirit of the FIVB 2001 Plan, AVC was the first to create five Zonal Associations at the 10th General Assembly in December 1993 prior to the FIVB Centennial Congress in September 1994.\n\n==Members==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable hlist\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:100%;\"\n! {{tooltip|Code|FIVB country code}} !! Association !! National teams !! [[International Olympic Committee|IOC]]<br/>member !! [[Olympic Council of Asia|OCA]]<br/>member !! [[Oceania National Olympic Committees|ONOC]]<br/>member\n|-\n|ASA ||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|ASA}} {{tooltip|American Samoa|American Samoa Volleyball Association}}||([[American Samoa men's national volleyball team|M]], [[American Samoa women's national volleyball team|W]])||{{yes}}||{{no}}||{{yes}}\n|-\n|AUS ||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Australian Volleyball Federation|{{tooltip|Australia|Australian Voll